---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Accessibility Statement | TEEI Corporate Cockpit"
  description="TEEI Corporate Cockpit accessibility statement and commitment to inclusive design"
>
  <div class="accessibility-statement">
    <h1>Accessibility Statement</h1>

    <section class="intro">
      <p class="lead">
        TEEI is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities.
        We are continually improving the user experience for everyone and applying the
        relevant accessibility standards.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Conformance Status</h2>
      <p>
        The <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG22/quickref/">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG)</a>
        defines requirements for designers and developers to improve accessibility for people with disabilities.
        It defines three levels of conformance: Level A, Level AA, and Level AAA.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>The TEEI Corporate Cockpit is partially conformant with WCAG 2.2 Level AA.</strong>
        Partially conformant means that some parts of the content do not fully conform to the accessibility standard.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Measures to Support Accessibility</h2>
      <p>TEEI takes the following measures to ensure accessibility of the Corporate Cockpit:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Include accessibility as part of our mission statement</li>
        <li>Include accessibility throughout our internal policies</li>
        <li>Integrate accessibility into our procurement practices</li>
        <li>Provide continual accessibility training for our staff</li>
        <li>Assign clear accessibility goals and responsibilities</li>
        <li>Employ formal accessibility quality assurance methods</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Accessibility Features</h2>

      <h3>Keyboard Navigation</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>All functionality is available via keyboard</li>
        <li>Visible focus indicators on all interactive elements</li>
        <li>Logical tab order throughout the application</li>
        <li>Skip links to bypass repetitive navigation</li>
        <li>No keyboard traps</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Screen Reader Support</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Semantic HTML5 elements and ARIA landmarks</li>
        <li>Descriptive labels for all interactive elements</li>
        <li>Alternative text for images and icons</li>
        <li>Live regions for dynamic content updates</li>
        <li>Proper heading hierarchy</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Visual Design</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Color contrast meets WCAG AA standards (minimum 4.5:1 for normal text)</li>
        <li>Information not conveyed by color alone</li>
        <li>Text can be resized up to 200% without loss of functionality</li>
        <li>Responsive design for various screen sizes</li>
        <li>Dark mode support</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Touch and Mobile</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Touch targets meet minimum size of 44x44 pixels</li>
        <li>Mobile-friendly navigation</li>
        <li>Responsive design for all devices</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Compatibility</h2>
      <p>
        The TEEI Corporate Cockpit is designed to be compatible with the following assistive technologies:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Screen Readers:</strong> NVDA, JAWS, VoiceOver, TalkBack</li>
        <li><strong>Browsers:</strong> Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge (latest 2 versions)</li>
        <li><strong>Operating Systems:</strong> Windows 10+, macOS 11+, iOS 14+, Android 10+</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The platform is designed to work with assistive technologies and the last two major
        versions of popular browsers and operating systems.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Known Limitations</h2>
      <p>
        Despite our best efforts to ensure accessibility of the TEEI Corporate Cockpit,
        there may be some limitations. Below is a description of known limitations and potential solutions:
      </p>

      <div class="limitation">
        <h3>Charts and Data Visualizations</h3>
        <p><strong>Issue:</strong> Some interactive charts may not be fully accessible to screen reader users.</p>
        <p><strong>Workaround:</strong> We provide data tables as alternatives for all visualizations. Use the "View Data Table" button below each chart.</p>
        <p><strong>Status:</strong> In progress - we are working on improving chart accessibility.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="limitation">
        <h3>PDF Exports</h3>
        <p><strong>Issue:</strong> Generated PDF reports may not be fully tagged for screen readers.</p>
        <p><strong>Workaround:</strong> Use the HTML version of reports for better accessibility.</p>
        <p><strong>Status:</strong> Planned for Q2 2025.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="limitation">
        <h3>Video Content</h3>
        <p><strong>Issue:</strong> Some instructional videos may lack captions or audio descriptions.</p>
        <p><strong>Workaround:</strong> Text transcripts are available for all videos.</p>
        <p><strong>Status:</strong> We are adding captions to all new and existing videos.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Feedback and Contact Information</h2>
      <p>
        We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of the TEEI Corporate Cockpit.
        Please let us know if you encounter accessibility barriers:
      </p>

      <div class="contact-info">
        <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:accessibility@teei-platform.com">accessibility@teei-platform.com</a></p>
        <p><strong>Phone:</strong> +47 XXX XX XXX (Norway)</p>
        <p><strong>Address:</strong> TEEI Platform AS, Oslo, Norway</p>
        <p><strong>Response Time:</strong> We aim to respond to accessibility feedback within 5 business days.</p>
      </div>

      <h3>What to Include in Your Report</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Description of the accessibility barrier</li>
        <li>Page or feature where the issue occurs</li>
        <li>Assistive technology being used (if applicable)</li>
        <li>Browser and operating system</li>
        <li>Steps to reproduce the issue</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Formal Complaints</h2>
      <p>
        If you are not satisfied with our response to your accessibility concern,
        you may file a complaint with the relevant national or regional authority:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Norway:</strong> Norwegian Digitalisation Agency (Digdir)</li>
        <li><strong>UK:</strong> Equality and Human Rights Commission (EHRC)</li>
        <li><strong>EU:</strong> European Commission - Digital Single Market</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Technical Specifications</h2>
      <p>
        Accessibility of the TEEI Corporate Cockpit relies on the following technologies
        to work with the particular combination of web browser and any assistive technologies
        or plugins installed on your computer:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>HTML5</li>
        <li>CSS3</li>
        <li>JavaScript (ES2022+)</li>
        <li>WAI-ARIA 1.2</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        These technologies are relied upon for conformance with the accessibility standards used.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Assessment Approach</h2>
      <p>
        TEEI assessed the accessibility of the Corporate Cockpit by the following approaches:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Self-evaluation:</strong> Internal testing by our development team</li>
        <li><strong>Automated testing:</strong> axe-core, Pa11y, and Lighthouse</li>
        <li><strong>Manual testing:</strong> Keyboard navigation and screen reader testing</li>
        <li><strong>User testing:</strong> Testing with users who rely on assistive technologies</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Continuous Improvement</h2>
      <p>
        We are committed to continuously improving the accessibility of our platform.
        Our accessibility efforts include:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Quarterly accessibility audits</li>
        <li>Regular automated testing in our CI/CD pipeline</li>
        <li>Staff training on accessibility best practices</li>
        <li>User feedback integration</li>
        <li>Accessibility considerations in all new features</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Date</h2>
      <p>
        This accessibility statement was created on <strong>14 November 2025</strong>.
        It was last reviewed on <strong>14 November 2025</strong>.
      </p>
      <p>
        This statement will be reviewed and updated quarterly or when significant changes
        are made to the platform.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="cta">
      <h2>Help Us Improve</h2>
      <p>
        Your feedback is essential to improving accessibility. If you have suggestions
        or encounter any issues, please don't hesitate to reach out.
      </p>
      <a href="mailto:accessibility@teei-platform.com" class="btn-primary">Contact Accessibility Team</a>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .accessibility-statement {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-foreground);
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-foreground);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border);
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-foreground);
  }

  .intro {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-foreground);
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  ul {
    margin-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  a:hover,
  a:focus {
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .limitation {
    background-color: var(--color-background);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary);
    padding: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .limitation h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .contact-info {
    background-color: var(--color-background);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .contact-info p {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .cta {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 2rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary) 0%, #0052a3 100%);
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .cta h2 {
    color: white;
    border: none;
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .cta p {
    color: white;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.75rem 2rem;
    background-color: white;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    transition: transform 0.2s;
  }

  .btn-primary:hover,
  .btn-primary:focus {
    transform: scale(1.05);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .accessibility-statement {
      padding: 1rem 0.5rem;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    .lead {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
    }
  }
</style>
